FBIS4-42368 "drweu107__a94004" FBIS-WEU-94-107-A Daily Report 3 June 1994 ANNEX International Affairs Vatican Requests UN Security Zone Around Kabgayi, Rwanda Vatican Requests UN Security Zone Around Kabgayi, Rwanda BR0206113194 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1543 GMT 1 Jun 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BR0206113194 Rome ANSAMAIL Database English BFN [Unattributed article: "Vatican/Rwanda: Holy See Wants UN Security Zone at Kagbayi"] [Text] (ANSA) New York, June 1 -- The Holy See on Wednesday [1 June] asked the United Nations Security Council to set up a security zone around Kabgayi, the religious community in southwestern Rwanda where an estimated 38,000 refugees of the Tutsi tribe have sought shelter from Hutu militias. "To save 38,000 lives, the UN must declare Kabgayi a security zone and must ban the entry of armed units there," the Vatican's UN representative, Renato Raffaele Martino, said.
